### Avoiding Nested Buttons with Triggers

To prevent hydration errors from nested `<button>` elements, use the `render` prop on trigger components (like `DropdownMenuTrigger`, `AlertDialogTrigger`, etc.) when the trigger itself should be a styled button.

**Correct Usage:**
Pass the button component you want to use as the trigger to the `render` prop. The children of the trigger will be rendered inside that button.

```tsx
// Correct: Use `render` prop on the Trigger
<DropdownMenu>
  <DropdownMenuTrigger render={<Button variant="ghost" size="icon" />}>
    <MoreHorizontal />
  </DropdownMenuTrigger>
  <DropdownMenuContent>
    {/* ... */}
  </DropdownMenuContent>
</DropdownMenu>
```

**Incorrect Usage:**
Avoid `asChild` on triggers (as it can lead to nested buttons or unrecognized prop errors with this project's Base UI components) and do not wrap a button component directly.

```tsx
// Incorrect: Causes nested <button> error
<DropdownMenuTrigger>
  <Button>Trigger</Button>
</DropdownMenuTrigger>

// Incorrect: `asChild` can also lead to errors if not supported correctly
<DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>
  <Button>Trigger</Button>
</DropdownMenuTrigger>
```
